# Project registry for this FeishuOPC instance.
#
# One JSON object per line. Every project this instance serves must be
# declared here (or be auto-discoverable via ``project-adapters/*.json``).
# FeishuOPC code itself has **no hardcoded project identifiers**.
#
# Fields:
# - ``project_id`` (required, string) — stable identifier used everywhere
#   (progress-sync adapters, code-write policies, workflow artifacts).
# - ``display_name`` (optional) — human label; defaults to project_id.
# - ``project_repo_root`` (optional) — absolute path (``~`` expanded) to
#   the target project's checkout. Required if you want workflow artifacts
#   to land in the real repo or the code-write tool to modify source files.
#   If omitted, workflow artifacts fall back to the sandbox
#   ``project_knowledge/<project_id>/`` inside this FeishuOPC checkout.
# - ``is_default`` (optional, bool) — the default project for this
#   instance. Exactly one project should be marked default. Alternatively,
#   set the ``DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID`` env var / ``settings.default_project_id``
#   to override.
# - Any other fields are preserved in ``Project.extra`` for future use.
#
# Lines beginning with "#" and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Rename this file to projects.jsonl. The production file is gitignored;
# this example is committed.
{"project_id":"exampleapp","display_name":"ExampleApp","project_repo_root":"~/Documents/Github/ExampleApp","is_default":true}
